Use|camera.full/camera.FREE_MODE|to enable the free camera mode
Use|camera.full/camera.FOCUS_MODE|to switch to focus mode
Use|camera.full/camera.GAME_MODE|to enable game mode
Use|camera.full/camera.GAIA_SCENE_MODE|to enter Gaia scene mode
Use|camera.full/camera.SPACECRAFT_MODE|to enter spacecraft mode
|action.toggle/element.debugmode|displays debug information
Use|action.search|to search objects by name
||The velocity of the camera is proportional to the distance from the Sun
Press|action.pauseresume|to start and stop the time
Press|action.dividetime|to slow down the pace of time
Press|action.doubletime|to speed up the pace of time
Use|action.loadcatalog|to load catalogs in VOTable or CSV at runtime
To show help use|action.help|
Use|action.gotoobject|to immediately move to the current focus object
Show and hide the minimap with|action.toggle/gui.minimap.title|
|double-click|on an object to select it
Show the preferences window with|action.preferences|
You can always go back home with|action.home|
You can reset the time with|action.resettime|
Control the visibility of each element from the visibility pane:|action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.visibility|
Create and edit bookmarks using the bookmarks pane:|action.expandcollapse.pane/gui.bookmarks|
Use|action.toggle/element.stereomode|to enter stereographic mode
Use|action.toggle/element.planetarium|to enter planetarium mode
Use|action.toggle/element.360|to enter panorama mode
You can disable all UI with|action.toggle/element.cleanmode|
Please send us a bug report if the program crashes:|gitlab.com/langurmonkey/gaiasky/issues|
||You can scale up the UI for HiDPI screens in the interface preferences
||Enable or disable post-processing effects in the graphics preferences
||Start Gaia Sky with '--noscript' to prevent the creation of the scripting server
||Start Gaia Sky with '-c' to show the catalog chooser window at startup
||Start Gaia Sky with '-d' to show the download manager at startup
||Some planets and moons have elevation data and gravity in Game mode
||Gaia Sky can use SAMP to interoperate with other astronomical software packages

